The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro briefs

 Ornaments worth Rs 1.5 lakh were looted from a temple on Rajendralal Mitra Road, near Thanthania Kalibari, in north Calcutta, on Monday night. The theft was detected on Tuesday morning when the priest opened the temple. Police said the burglars had to break three locks before they could lay their hands on the gold and silver ornaments of goddess Gandheswari.

 A truck crushed to death a husband and a wife on National Highway 6 in Sankrail, Howrah, on Monday morning. Their three-year-old son escaped unhurt. Biswanath Das, 30, and Pampa, 25, residents of Batanagar, were heading home from a relatives house in Uluberia on a motorcycle when the mishap occurred. The truck driver fled.

 The Dalai Lama is slated to visit the city in mid-January to take part in the 40th anniversary celebrations of Young Mens Welfare Society. He will speak on Ethics in Human Development.

 A petition was moved in the high court on Tuesday seeking an order to restrain Trinamul Congress from enforcing the bandh on Thursday and Friday. The division bench of Chief Justice V.S. Sirpurkar told petitioners advocate Idris Ali that the matter would be heard on Wednesday. 




